{"TopicId":216781,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"New Burn Timer Displays Time Incorrectly When the Node is Above 99 Days.","CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-22T03:22:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-22T03:22:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP2 Version:\u003C/strong\u003E 0.1.2.0.22258\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOperating System:\u003C/strong\u003E Windows 10\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECPU\u002BGPU\u002BRAM: \u003C/strong\u003Ei9 9900K\u002B3070ti\u002B32GB\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMods Used:\u003C/strong\u003E None\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EScreenshot:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kH7wIpj.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002238.88\u0022 height=\u0022173\u0022 width=\u0022445\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/kH7wIpj.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EVideo Evidence:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nShowing the issue going from 99 days which is good to 99\u002B when it isn\u0027t.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/QPr2Uk-fsLk\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/QPr2Uk-fsLk\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESave File from Video:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/ni2ngkwfwjn8gg5/0120BurnTimerDisplayWrongSave.zip?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/ni2ngkwfwjn8gg5/0120BurnTimerDisplayWrongSave.zip?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-01T04:38:02Z\u0022 title=\u002206/01/2023 04:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 1, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Filed.Teeth","CreatedById":178610,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-22T03:35:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like it switches to two lines from being full when it adds the extra digit, and the text is right-justified so the \u0022T-\u0022 is pushed back to line 1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember was it diff in Patch 0 and 1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-22T11:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224275719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221682134501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178610\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Filed.Teeth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Filed.Teeth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember was it diff in Patch 0 and 1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPatch 2 has a new display. I never saw that happen with 0.1.0.0 or 0.1.1.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-22T14:18:18Z\u0022 title=\u002204/22/2023 02:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Filed.Teeth","CreatedById":178610,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T00:17:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that I\u0027m looking at it, I\u0027ve noticed something else. No allowance for years. The \u0022Start Burn In\u0022 counter just rolls over to 0 after 424:05:59:59.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the same in reverse, so if you set a node 435 days out, it will count down from 10 days, then switch to\u00A0424:05:59:59 when the 10 hits zero.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and on two lines as long as there\u0027s 3 digits in the days.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-23T00:18:57Z\u0022 title=\u002204/23/2023 12:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Filed.Teeth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T02:27:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224276039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221682209062\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178610\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Filed.Teeth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Filed.Teeth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that I\u0027m looking at it, I\u0027ve noticed something else. No allowance for years. The \u0022Start Burn In\u0022 counter just rolls over to 0 after 424:05:59:59.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the same in reverse, so if you set a node 435 days out, it will count down from 10 days, then switch to\u00A0424:05:59:59 when the 10 hits zero.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and on two lines as long as there\u0027s 3 digits in the days.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah there are other places that have similar issues. Like the AP/PE below the navball being limited to 6 hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-22T16:23:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/217807-ksp2-patch-notes-v0130\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EThis has been fixed as of v0.1.3.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}